article.headline: UC Riverside 72, Cal Poly 63
article.story: ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Nate Carter scored 19 points to lead UC Riverside to a 72-63 victory over Cal Poly in the first round of the Big West Conference tournament Wednesday night. Vili Morton and Rickey Porter added 16 points apiece and Morton grabbed a season-high 14 rebounds for the fifth-seeded Highlanders (11-16), who won their first tournament game as a member of NCAA Division I. UC Riverside will play fourth-seeded Idaho in Thursday night's quarterfinals. Varnie Dennis, the conference's leading scorer, had 14 points and a career-best 15 rebounds for the eighth-seeded Mustangs (11-16), who were finalists in last year's tournament. Shane Schilling added 13 points. Cal Poly rallied from a 34-25 deficit to take a 36-35 lead with 14:02 to play. But Carter scored six points during a 10-2 run that gave UC Riverside a 45-38 lead with 10:39 left. The Mustangs missed 20 of 32 field-goal attempts in the second half.
